What makes the holidays so special? Hot chocolate ‚òïÔ∏è
Here my healthy protein PB hot chocolate recipe with a Christmas twist and vegan frothy milk‚¨áÔ∏è
- Boil 50 ml of water with a bag of chai tea
- add 150 ml of almond milk (or of your choice)
- bring to boil and take the tea bag out
- add a tea spoon of raw cacao powder (I always use @vivoo.it | AD)
- add half a tsp of honey
- add half a tea spoon of PB (or nut butter of your choice)
- add 10g of protein powder (I used vegan peanut butter flavoured)
- add 5g of rice flour
- stir until smooth (on a very low flame)
- boil 50ml of soy milk, use a cappuccino electric frother on the higher speed
- top the hot chocolate with froth, pb, cinnamon and cacao nibs or as liked üòä

I get asked a lot about how me and Aiyu deal with long distance.

Truth is at the beginning I didn‚Äôt even know how it would go. I‚Äôm someone that gets easily detached with distance, I don‚Äôt like to stay on the phone, I shout down feelings. So you understand why I was worried.

But see, if something, s o m e o n e , is worth it, you make it work, you do the work. 
Even if it means to come all the way to Bali to spend a week together when you haven‚Äôt seen each other in months or doing things like swimming in sharks (fake) infested water to make each other feel supported and happy!
